iell der Vorschlag Schefflers, dass die Wach`sche Exemplifikationsmethode auch eine taugliche Gesetzestechnik zur Vermeidung von sog. "horizontaler Kasuistik" sei.  aThis work considers the legal techniques used in the German Criminal Code for penalty increases, especially the standard example method for severe criminal offences. The advantage of the exemplifications method by Wach in comparison to the standard example technique is presented and explained, namely that this method can generally be a successful compromise between the casuistic and generalized legal technique.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAggravating circumstancesxGermany. 0aAggravating circumstanceszGermany. 0aJudgments, CriminalxGermany. 0aJudgments, CriminalzGermany. 0aJudicial discretionxGermany. 0aJudicial discretionzGermany. 4aStrafrecht. 4aWach, Adolf. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh  aCriminal Law.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2009z9783899496871oZDB-23-DGC0 cprintz978389949748940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978389949749640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783899497496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783899497496/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2009  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014